        <h2>Breadcrumbs</h2>
        <p>Breadcrumbs come in handy to show a navigation trail for users clicking through your site.</p>
        <p>To make a set of breadcrumb links, just add series of <Code>@("<BreadcrumbItem>")</Code> inside <Code>@("<Breadcrumb>")</Code> component, and then add links inside of the <Code>@("<BreadcrumbItem>")</Code> elements. The current page doesn't require a link or a class, but you should add some explanatory text for AT that indicates which item is the current page. To mark a disabled item, add the atribute <Code>Disable="true"</Code> to the <Code>@("<BreadcrumbItem>")</Code>, and just use plain text instead of a link.</p>
